  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Near infrared spectroscopy offers the possibility of noninvasive and continuous bedside
      investigation of cerebral oxygenation in newborn infants. Using this technique we
      investigated the relationship between changes in cerebral oxygenation and hemodynamics, and
      changes in some physiological variables during blood transfusion in anaemic preterm infants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
